Week #1 Results
The first week of fishing league saw 44 walleyes brought to the scale for 99.92  lbs.  Taking top honors was Trent Jorgenson and Tony Crotty (sub) weighing in 3 fish for  13.35  lbs.  They also had the big fish of the night,  a 9.64 pounder.  Second place went to Logan Spray and Mikkal Erickson with 5 fish for 12.97 lbs.  Third place was Matt Fischer and Jeff Rieke with 3 fish for 12.03 lbs.  Fourth place was  Sam Thomas and Scott VanOverbeke with  5 fish for 10.8  lbs.  Fifth place was Cody Enger and Patrick Miller with 5 fish for 9.57 lbs.
Week #2 Results
Due to inclement weather last week, fishing league was cancelled.  The second week of fishing league saw 31 walleyes brought to the scale for 100.93 lbs.  Taking top honors was Pete McGinty and Shannon Larson weighing in  4 fish for 14.09 lbs.   Second place went to Tony Malmquist and Jordan Fischer with 3 fish for 12.34 lbs.  Third place was  Logan Spray and Mikkal Erickson with 3 fish for 10.41 lbs.  Fourth place was  Cody Enger and Patrick Miller with 3 fish for 9.84 lbs.  Fifth place was Jay Kleven and Darin Lund with 1 fish for 8.61 lbs.  They also had the big fish of the night.​
​ Week #3 Results
The third week of fishing league saw 38 walleyes brought to the scale for 93.68 lbs.  Taking top honors was Tony Malmquist and Jordan Fischer weighing in 5 fish for 15.24 lbs.   Second place went to Dave Cornelius and Steffan Sticklestad with 5 fish for 13.24 lbs.  Third place was Eric Spray and Adam Spray with 5 fish for 10.47 lbs.  Fourth place was Tom Ludvigson and Dustin Fernholz with 3 fish for 10.16 lbs.  Fifth place was  Jack Anderson and Tony Meseck with 3 fish for 7.36 lbs.  Big fish for the night went to Corey Reiffenberger and Lainey Reiffenberger with a 6.38 lber.
​ Week #4 Results
The fourth week of fishing league saw 40 walleyes brought to the scale for 96.15 lbs.  Taking top honors was Bob Hoium and Austin Hiepler weighing in 4 fish for 14.03 lbs.   Second place went to Logan Spray and Mikkal Erickson with 4 fish f0r 11.73 lbs.  Third place was Tom Halvorson and Gage Halvorson with 1 fish for 9.33 lbs.  They also had the big fish of the night a 9.33 lber.  Fourth place was Corey Joyce and (sub) Jeff Reuss with 5 fish for 7.70 lbs.  Fifth place was Sedrick Borsgard and Ryan Anderson with 2 fish for 6.76 lbs.  They also caught a sheepshead that tipped the scales at over 28.4 lbs!
Week #5 Results
The fifth week of fishing league saw 32 walleyes brought to the scale for 63.97 lbs.  Taking top honors was Tom Ludvigson and Dustin Fernholz weighing in 5 fish for 13.64 lbs.   They also had the big fish of the night a 5.89 lber.  Second place went to Dave Cornelius and Steffan Sticklestad with 5 fish f0r 7.31 lbs.  Third place was Jack Anderson and Tony Meseck with 3 fish for 6.05 lbs.  Fourth place was Matt Fischer and Jeff Rieke with 2 fish for  5.46 lbs.  Fifth place was Eric Spray and Adam Spray with 4 fish for 5.02 lbs.
​​ ​
End of the Year Results
The 2024 fishing league has come to an end.  This year''s league was cut short by two weeks due to weather.  There were  185 walleyes weighed in for a total of  454.65 pounds.  This year''s first place team was Tony Malmquist and Jordan Fischer with a total weight of 47.75 lbs.  Second Place went to Logan Spray and Mikkal Erickson who had a total weight of 44.44 lbs.  Third Place was Tom Ludvigson and Dustin Fernholz with a total weight of 36.26 lbs.  Congratulations to the top 3 teams.  Thank you to Corey Joyce, Corey Reiffenberger and Steve Benson for running the fishing league!' WHERE id = 3;

